// NMI arrives during an INTA cycle. NMI takes priority over INT — the test
// is whether NMI is queued cleanly during INTA (without corrupting the INTA)
// or whether the model handles concurrent edges in the right order. After
// INTA completes (RST 38h in IM 1), NMI should be accepted; expect a NMI
// ack M-cycle before the IM1 ISR runs to a final HALT.
@0000
ED 56              // IM 1
FB                 // EI
00 00 00 00 00     // NOPs (loop)
C3 03 00           // JP 0x0003
@0038
76                 // HALT (IM1 vector)
@0066
76                 // HALT (NMI vector)
